dismissalText.commentary: Forster Mutizwa run out (Shakib Al Hasan/Mushfiqur Rahim) 27 (38b 2x4 0x6 57m) SR: 71.05

dismissalComment.html: gone! superb work from extra cover, and guess who it is, it is Shakib Al Hasan, low full toss hit hard, he thought it had enough to go past extra cover, but Shakib was around there to put in a big dive to his right and stop the ball, Mutizwa was more than half way down the track by then, and it was too late to get back as Shakib fired in an accurate throw to Rahim, can any performance get more all-round than that?

commentTextItems.html: all over for Zimbabwe, that is the game for Bangladesh, Meth is not going to come out to bat, widish delivery, he goes after it from the crease and hits it to backward point

commentPostTextItems.html: This is Abhishek Purohit signing off for one final time in this series. Keep joining us for more action from around the cricketing world. Cheers!
Taylor gets the series trophy, Meth joins in as well feeling his sore mouth gingerly. A happy Zimbabwe unit pose with the trophy and that brings us to an end of this series.

Brendan Taylor: "Bit disappointed with the way we ended but pretty chuffed with the series win, we will enjoy it. We played well as a collective unit, guys put their hands up and batted deep, bowlers did well and we fielded well. We are in a good place right now [with the depth in the squad] and it is nice to have options. We will get back to some hard work and see where we can improve on for the Pakistan series. Massive thank you to the crowd, they have come out and are getting bigger, hopefully we can put some smiles on their faces."

Brian Vitori is the Man of the Series for his match-winning performances that gave Zimbabwe the series. Vitori: "We have done all the hard work, had two months of preparation, I am not surprised that we did well. I was just having a problem with my shin and had to rest it [for the last two games]. Hopefully I will be ready for the Test against Pakistan."

Shakib Al Hasan is the Man of the Match. Shakib: "All the boys showed some character that we are not here just to play the game. It was painful (the injured finger), not too much worry, it should be alright. Newcomers have shown lots of promise, our fast bowlers have done well throughout the series. Everything came well in the last two games, We were coming off a break from international cricket, so it was not going to be easy for the guys."

Handshakes all around, that is the end of the series. So Bangladesh coming back in this series after it was gone, the third game was within their reach, it was one straight hit away but they could not do it. Poor batting performance from Zimbabwe today, they could do nothing against the spinners once Sibanda fell. Shakib doing it again for Bangladesh, 216 runs in the series at an average of 54 (bettered only by Sibanda), and six wickets at under five an over

dismissalComment.html: gone right away, Rubel strikes first ball, Taylor pushing away from his body, a problem he has had throughout this series, holding its line some way outside off from a length, no need to do anything with it, but Taylor goes poking limply and Rahim gleefully snaps up the edge

dismissalText.long: c Tamim Iqbal b Shakib Al Hasan
dismissalText.commentary: Vusi Sibanda c Tamim Iqbal b Shakib Al Hasan 34 (44b 5x4 2x6 53m) SR: 77.27

dismissalComment.html: Sibanda is gone, off a mistimed pull, not for the first time in the series, rocked back as he saw one angled in short in to him, but got the pull off the back of the bat towards short third man who took the dolly

headshotImage.caption: Abdur Razzak player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Abdur Razzak player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Hamilton Masakadza lbw b Abdur Razzak 28 (43b 3x4 0x6 58m) SR: 65.11

dismissalComment.html: gone leg before, this time the appeal is upheld, shuffling forward to one coming in with the angle, struck in front of middle and leg, that would have hit leg stump, and he is sent on his way

dismissalText.commentary: Tatenda Taibu lbw b Shakib Al Hasan 7 (14b 1x4 0x6 14m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: could not get plumber that that, Taibu trying to drag the sweep from off stump, Shakib angles it in full from wide of the crease, pitched around middle and off, Taibu misses with the big swing, and that was hitting off and middle, more middle than off

headshotImage.longCaption: Forster Mutizwa player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Forster Mutizwa player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Forster Mutizwa player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Forster Mutizwa run out (Shakib Al Hasan/Mushfiqur Rahim) 27 (38b 2x4 0x6 57m) SR: 71.05

dismissalComment.html: gone! superb work from extra cover, and guess who it is, it is Shakib Al Hasan, low full toss hit hard, he thought it had enough to go past extra cover, but Shakib was around there to put in a big dive to his right and stop the ball, Mutizwa was more than half way down the track by then, and it was too late to get back as Shakib fired in an accurate throw to Rahim, can any performance get more all-round than that?

headshotImage.caption: Imrul Kayes player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Imrul Kayes player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Malcolm Waller c Imrul Kayes b Mahmudullah 51 (70b 4x4 0x6 78m) SR: 72.85

dismissalComment.html: that is it for Waller and for Zimbabwe I say, down on the knee and tries to slog-sweep over midwicket, gets it straight to the man in the deep, been an entertaining innings, and has brought Zimbabwe back a shade but he has given it away

headshotImage.caption: Imrul Kayes player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Imrul Kayes player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Elton Chigumbura c Imrul Kayes b Mahmudullah 1 (5b 0x4 0x6 7m) SR: 20

dismissalComment.html: the tamest of tame dismissals, shuffled across to a short delivery turning in, seemed to be in two minds whether to crack it over midwicket or play it out, in the end did something in between and pushed it straight to the man there

headshotImage.caption: Abdur Razzak player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Abdur Razzak player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Prosper Utseya c Abdur Razzak b Mahmudullah 7 (12b 0x4 0x6 7m) SR: 58.33

dismissalComment.html: another one goes, Utseya departs now, shortish one, he tries to go back in the crease and pull it through square leg, tame top edge, swirls up tamely and shot fine leg is waiting under it

stories.seoTitle: Zimbabwe v Bangladesh: Keegan Meth suffers unfortunate mouth injury
stories.summary: Zimbabwe seamer Keegan Meth has suffered a laceration to the lower lip and lost three upper row teeth following a ghastly incident at the end of the Bangladesh innings in the final ODI in Bulawayo
